## ERROR TIPS

### AttributeError: 'str' object has no attribute 'prototype_name'
- This error occurs when you are trying to access the `prototype_name` attribute of a string object, but this attribute only exists for Prototype objects.
- Ensure that you are passing the actual Prototype object (e.g., from `game.item_prototypes`) to the function instead of just the string name of the item.

### Errors when using extracting but being too far
- Make sure to move to the target entity where you want to extract from before extracting items

### Errors when placing into a tile which is occupied by another entity
- Ensure you can place a entity to a tile before attempting placing
